'''Ɛtumba ya Kivu''' ezalí [[ɛtumba]] ya [[Kivu ya Nole|Kivu]] ya [[Kongó-Kinsásá|Kongó Demokratiki]]. Ebandí 2003 na nsima [[Ɛtumba ya Kongó ya míbalé]].<ref>[http://www.hrw.org/english/docs/2006/01/31/congo12579.htm {{en}} Arrest Laurent Nkunda For War Crimes], Human Rights Watch, 1 febwáli 2006.</ref> Mibundi bazalí mibundi [[CNDP]], [[mai-mai]],<ref>[http://afrikarabia2.blogs.courrierinternational.com/archive/2007/12/27/nord-kivu-rdc-violents-combats-entre-milices-mai-mai-et-les.html {{fr}} Afrikarabia: Violents combats entre milices mai-mai et rebelles. 27 dɛcɛ́mbɛ 2007.]</ref> mibundi [[FDLR]], mibundi ya lɛ́ta, [[MONUC]] mpé ntángo mosúsu mibundi ya [[Angola]].<ref>[http://www.france24.com/en/20081108-dr-congo-troops-shore-front-line-positions {{en}} Simon, Ben: DR Congo troops shore up front-line positions, France 24. 8 novɛ́mbɛ 2008.]</ref> Mibundi ya lɛ́ta bapillí bambóka.<ref>[http://www.lesoir.be/actualite/monde/kagame-recoit-des-emissaires-2008-10-29-655437.shtml {{fr}} Le Soir: L'armée congolaise abandonne Goma, 28 ɔkɔtɔ́bɛ 2008.]</ref> <ref>{{de}} Neue Zürcher Zeitung, 22/23 novɛ́mbɛ 2008, éditorial.</ref>

